  "contentHtml": "\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <p><img src=\"https://health.economictimes.indiatimes.com/Themes/Release/theme4/images/icons/et-default-user.svg\" alt=\"Online Bureau\">\n                                            \n                                        </p>\n                                                                        \n                                                                                    <ul>\n                                                                                                    <li>\n                                                                                                                                                                            <a>Online Bureau</a>\n                                                            \n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                                                                                                            </li>\n                                                                                                                                                    <li><a href=\"/agency/88675629/ETHealthWorld\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ETHealthWorld</a></li>\n                                                                                            </ul>\n                                                                                <ul>\n                                                                                            <li>Published On Jul 23, 2026 at 07:26 PM IST</li>\n                                                                                                                                </ul>\n                                    \n                                                                            \n                                                                        \n                                \n                                \n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Mumbai: Healthcare diagnostic chain, Thyrocare reported a 24 per cent year on year growth in consolidated revenue at Rs 240.02 cr for the first quarter ending June this year.Ebitda for the quarter stood at Rs 77.27 cr, up 34 per cent year on year, while profit after tax also increased 34 per cent to Rs 51.33 cr.The diagnostic chain said growth was primarily driven by its pathology segment, as franchise revenue grew by 27 per cent year on year, while partnership segment recorded 26 per cent year on year growth.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>In the three month period, Thyrocare processed 55.2 million tests, up 28 per cent year-on-year, making it the largest diagnostic test volume processor in India.</p>\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>The company also expanded into the specialty diagnostics segment in the quarter, beginning with  Allergy and Genomics testing.  Rahul Guha, MD &amp; CEO, Thyrocare Technologies said, “Thyrocare reported a strong performance this quarter, driven by continued focus on operational efficiency, network expansion, and value-driven diagnostics.”</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>“During the period, we also strengthened our specialty portfolio with the addition of allergy testing and entry into genomics through the launch of NIPT, with a phased expansion of the test menu underway. Thyrocare continues to expand its reach in underserved regions and scale its franchise and partner network, while remaining committed to delivering high-quality, affordable healthcare services across India” </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                                                            <!-- <li>By <span>Online Bureau</span>,</li> -->\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <li>By\n                                                                                            <a>Online Bureau</a>\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                        , \n                                                                                    </li>\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/88675629/ETHealthWorld\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ETHealthWorld</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On Jul 23, 2026 at 07:26 PM IST</li> -->\n                                    <li>Published On Jul 23, 2026 at 07:26 PM IST</li>\n                                    <!-- <li class=\"desktop-view\">1 min read</li> -->\n                                </ul>\n                            \n                                        \n\n                    \n\n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n                                            \n                                        <!-- Comment Section -->\n\n                    \n                      \n    \n            <p>\n                </p